    "Next, the minimum-energy structure was obtained with the Limited-memory Broyden-Fletcher-Goldfarb-Shanno optimizer 88.",
    "Then, Langevin dynamics simulations were run at 2,000 K for 10 ns with a 0.5 fs time step and a friction constant of 0.01.",
    "Snapshots and properties were recorded every 0.5 ps (1,000 time steps).",
    "Ring structures of varying sizes were identified and counted with our in-house code MolFind.",
    "Considering that the distance between bonded atoms can fluctuate, a 0.02 Å buffer was utilized when scanning C-C bonds so that any pair of carbon atoms that has distance smaller than 1.72 Å (two times the covalent radius of carbon atom plus the buffer) were considered bonded."
